OL,3,CKing Charles opens wing named after
OL,4,Chimself at Centre of Islamic Studies
OL,6,FITV News Meridian's Wesley Smith has
OL,7,Fbeen in Oxford to find out more.
OL,9,FKing Charles described the Oxford
OL,10,FCentre for Islamic Studies as a
OL,11,F"beacon of Islamic scholarship" when
OL,12,Fhe visited to celebrate the 40th
OL,13,Fanniversary of the institution.
OL,15,FCrowds gathered to watch the King open
OL,16,Fa new wing named after himself.
OL,18,FHis Majesty, who is a patron of the
OL,19,Fcentre, was welcomed by its director,
OL,20,FDr Farhan Nizami and Lord Hague, the
OL,21,Fnew Chancellor of Oxford University.
